-- Flooding Kills at Least 23 People in China's Sichuan Province, Xinhua Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-18T23:05:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-18/flooding-kills-at-least-23-people-in-china-s-sichuan-province-xinhua-says.html

          
          
             At least 23 people have been killed
in flooding in the southwestern Chinese province of Sichuan
sparked by rainstorms that began late on July 16, the official
Xinhua News Agency reported.  
 Another 30 people were missing as of late yesterday, Xinhua
reported, citing the provincial civil affairs department. More
than 586,000 people have been evacuated from their homes,
according to the report.  
          
          


  


        